# MCTS package

Game-agnostic Monte Carlo Tree Search library in TypeScript. Replaces or augments heuristic AI (e.g. Quarto `ai.ts`) while staying reusable across Smart Games SPAs.

**Authoritative API detail:** `specification.md` at the package root. Rules encode invariants; the spec is the reference.

## Directory map

```text
src/
  contracts/     Shared interfaces (main thread + worker)
  mcts/          MCTSEngine, SearchParameters, StopSignal
  coordinator/   MCTSSearchCoordinator, GameCoordinatorAdapter
  worker/        Message loop, heuristic registry
  worker-port/   Optional thin postMessage helper
  games/<name>/  Per-game adapters (later)
worker-entry.ts  Worker bundle entry
```

## Implementation phases (spec §17)

1. **Core** — contracts, `SearchParameters`, `MCTSEngine`, toy game (tic-tac-toe)
2. **Coordinator + worker** — `computeMove`, message protocol, `MCTSWorkerPort`
3. **Quarto** — game adapter + QuAIto integration (**additive** MCTS difficulty; keep heuristic `easy`–`brutal`)
4. **Polish** — diagnostics, profiling, docs

## v1 acceptance highlights (spec §18)

- Toy game: finds one-ply wins and blocks one-ply losses
- Worker search does not block the main thread
- Same `SearchParameters` + `seed` + stop point → same `bestMoveKey`
- **No game-specific imports** in `src/mcts/` or `src/contracts/`
- **No wall-clock timing** in `src/mcts/` or `src/worker/`
- Game apps call **`computeMove` / `stop` only** — never `postSearch` directly

## Locked decisions (spec §16)

- Turn-based only (no simultaneous moves)
- Per-app worker bundle; package name `@smart-games/mcts`
- Progress optional; `movePriorWeight` optional (expansion order uses `heuristicValue` in v1)
- **`PlayerId` is `0 | 1` (zero-based)** — app UI labels map at game adapter boundary only
- UCT and post-search ties: **random** among equals via search PRNG
- PRNG: **mulberry32**, one instance per search — never `Math.random()` in core

## Shared SPA rules

Symlinked `common-SPA.mdc` and `common-react-architecture.mdc` apply when integrating into React apps (QuAIto). They do **not** govern core library design — follow MCTS-specific rules for `src/mcts/`, `src/contracts/`, `src/coordinator/`, and `src/worker/`.

## QuAIto integration (Phase 3)

See QuAIto `.cursor/rules/quaito-ai.mdc`. Summary:
- Heuristic AI (`makeAIMove`, `easy`–`brutal`) must remain working — MCTS is an **additional user-selected difficulty**, not a replacement.
- App calls `MCTSSearchCoordinator.computeMove()` only; Quarto adapters may live in QuAIto or `src/games/quarto/`.
